  "prompt": "What are some free alternatives to Aha.io?",
  "response": "There are several free alternatives to Aha.io that you might consider for product management and roadmapping needs. While they may not all have the exact feature set of Aha.io, they offer various tools and functionalities that might suit your requirements:\n\n1. **Trello**: A popular project management tool that uses boards, lists, and cards to organize tasks. It\u2019s highly flexible and has a visually intuitive interface.\n\n2. **Asana**: This tool is great for managing tasks and projects with a team. It offers features like task assignments, due dates, and kanban boards.\n\n3. **ClickUp**: A versatile productivity platform that includes features for task management, time tracking, and goal setting. Their free plan includes a wide range of features.\n\n4. **Jira**: Primarily used for software development, Jira offers issue and project tracking functionalities. It\u2019s particularly helpful for agile teams.\n\n5. **Notion**: A flexible workspace for note-taking, task management, and project planning. It offers templates for roadmapping and more.\n\n6. **Monday.com**: A work operating system that provides customizable templates for project management. They offer a free plan with limited features.\n\n7. **Wrike**: Offers project management and collaboration tools. The free version is suitable for small teams.\n\n8. **Taiga**: An open-source project management tool geared toward agile development. It offers features for sprint planning, backlog management, and more.\n\n9. **Productboard**: While the free tier may be limited, it\u2019s designed specifically for product teams, with features for prioritization and customer feedback.\n\n10. **Backlog by Nulab**: A project management and collaboration tool for developers with features like Gantt charts, version control integration, and task management.\n\nWhen considering a free alternative, it\u2019s important to assess the specific features and limitations of each option to ensure they align well with your team\u2019s workflow and needs.",
